<h1>From Captain De Santerre</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">My General</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">[Cap-Franais, Saint-Domingue, 27 January 1776]<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0144-fn-0001" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0144-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>I am a french Officer, first Captain of my Regiment I have Served twenty four years, I have been in Germany all the Last war, when I thought to have reapd the fruits of my Long Service &amp; my fatigue, I have been most Cruelly used by a puissant Chief, against whom I have it not in my power to take my revenge, I have demanded justice, intrigue, money &amp; the great Credit of my adversary, have renderd my Complaints of no effect I have quitted forever a Country, where I have experienced Such heartbreaking vexations.</p>
<p>I pray you My General, to Let me Know whether you will grant me an Asylum, &amp; in your Service I will devote to your nation my blood, &amp; the Little fortune which I can pluck from the greedy hands which persecute me I will Serve your Country
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-03-03-02-pb-0200">[200]</span>
with all that Zeal &amp; fidelity which you have a right to expect from an Officer, whom honour has been the only Cause of his misfortunes.</p>
<p>Give me My General, the power, the Glory to die in deffense of your Laws &amp; your Liberty I will become one of your Citizens, I will with pleasure Seal with my blood, this title which I now Solicit from you, if the war Shoud Spare me, I will finish my days amongst your Countrymen, to whom I make account of attaching myself, by the most Sacred ties.</p>
<p>I burn to open the next Campaign with you nor do I desire that you will put the Least Confidence in me untill I have in the field of battle deserved it.<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0144-fn-0002" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0144-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0144-sn">

   <p>
Copy, translated from the French, in Stephen Moylans writing, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>; 
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
 Moylans translation omits the dateline, closing, and postscript of the <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>. See notes 1 and 2. The cover of the <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr> is addressed au Gnral des Provinces et des Troupes confdres de La nouvelle Angleterre en <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Amrique</span>. P. Moreau carried this letter to Providence and gave it to Nicholas Cooke who forwarded it to GW. For additional information about De Santerre and his proposals, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0243" class="document">Moreau to GW, 19 Feb. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0144-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0144-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>The dateline of the <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr> reads au Cap st Dommingue le 27 Janvier 1776.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0144-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0144-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>The text of the <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr> reads: Je suis officier francais, prmier Capitaine de mon Regiment; jai servi vingt-quatre ans; jai fait la guerre derniere en Allemagne. dans le moment ou je devais mattendre  receuillir les fruits de mes travaux, je me suis v cruellement outrag par un chef puissant contre le quel je navais point  prendre de vangeance. jai demand justice; la cabale, Largent et le crdit de mon adversaire ont rendu mes plaintes inutiles. je veux quitter pour jamais un Pas ou jessuie les plus sanglantes vxations.</p>


   <p>Je vous prie, mon Gnral, de me faire savoir Si vous vouls me donner un azile et du Service je consacrerai  votre Nation mon Sang et le peu de fortune que je pourrai tirer des mains avides qui me perscutent. je Servirai votre Patrie avec tout le zle et toute la fidlit que vous aurs droit dattendre dun officier dont lhonneur  caus Linfortune.</p>


   <p>donns moi, mon Gnral, des droits pour prir  la deffense de vos loix et de votre libert. je veux devenir un de vos Citoiens; je veux Scller de mon Sang le titre que je Sollicite aupres de vous. Si la Guerre mpargne, je finirai mes jours parmi vos compatriotes aux quels je compte mattacher par les liens les plus Sacrs.</p>


   <p>je brule douvrir avec vous la campagne prochaine; et je ne demanderai votre confiance quapres lavoir mrite Sur le champ de Bataille. Je suis avec un profond respect, Mon Gnral Votre tres humble et tres obeissant serviteur</p>


   <p style="margin-right: 1em; text-align: right;">De Santerre<br/>prmier Capitaine au Rgiment de la Martinique</p>

<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-03-03-02-pb-0201">[201]</span>

   <p style="text-indent: 0;">Je vous prie, Mon Gnral de prendre confiance dans le Jeune homme qui aura Lhonneur de vous remettre ma lettre et dajouter foi  tout cequil vous dira sur cequi me concerne.</p>

</div>
</div>
